stories.title: 'New perspective in my life'
stories.summary: Jacques Kallis hit his second century in as many days as he anchored South Africa to an emotional win against Zimbabwe

stories.title: Kallis century puts paid to Zimbabwe
stories.summary: Jacques Kallis scored a magnificent unbeaten 125, his 10th and highest one-day century, and his second in consecutive days, as South Africa bounced back from defeat in their opening match of the NatWest Series to record a comfortable 46-run victory
stories.byline: The Wisden Bulletin by Andrew Miller
